description:
The plan of redemption in Christ is seen in typology in the Bible, especially in the life of Abraham. What details in the story of Abraham’s sacrifice of Isaac provide insight into God’s relationship with us? What can we learn from the story of Abraham’s rescue of Lot? What is significant about the gift Melchizedek met Abraham with?

We are living on the threshold of final events. Do you trust God totally? If not, when will you develop that trust? Discover new lessons from the Bible symbolism in the story of Abraham and his relationship with God and draw nearer to God as you learn to trust Him completely.
